== Command Options

* -r — Raw output (for scripting / power user)
* -v — Verbose. See curl command
* -O — API JSON Output
* -J — API Parsed Output
* -H — API Response Headers
* -d — Dry run a command
* -x — Full debugging trace output

----
== Features

* Full manpage integrated help / doc
* Context sensitive
* 'user/repo' syntax
  * git hub clone 'g0v/g0v.tw'
  * @ → your-user-login
* Third Party Plugin Commands
  * carloslima/git-hub-travis
* Command Chaining
* Written all in Bash.
  * No joke!
  * Includes Bash JSON parser and Test Framework
  * Works instantly / anywhere
  * Bash is a cool new programming language!
